# API Test Automation Agent

Generate and modify Cypress API tests following the exact patterns in this project.

## Project layout

```
cypress/fixtures/hosts.json          ← base URLs per environment (dev/qa)
cypress/support/lib/<domain>.ts           ← one wrapper class per API domain
cypress/support/utils/requests.ts     ← HTTP helpers
cypress/support/utils/assertions.ts   ← verifyResponseTemplate / verifyResponseCode
cypress/support/utils/common.ts       ← readTestDataJson() / date helpers
cypress/support/utils/apiTracker.ts   ← debug tracker
cypress/fixtures/<domain>/        ← JSON fixtures (request + response template per endpoint)
cypress/e2e/api/<domain>.spec.ts  ← tests
```

## Wrapper class pattern (`cypress/support/lib/<domain>.ts`)

- Constructor accepts optional `baseUrl`
- Stores `baseUrl` from `cypress/fixtures/hosts.json` using `process.env.ENV || 'dev'`
- Uses Cypress request helpers from `cypress/support/utils/requests.ts`
- `initVariables()` loads fixtures via `readTestDataJson()` into public properties
- Exposes public request/response template properties for spec reuse

## Test data template rules

Response template files use these validation keywords:

| Keyword | Rule |
|---------|------|
| `"skip"` | Ignore field |
| `"should_not_be_null"` | Must not be null |
| `"only_chars"` | `/^[a-zA-Z]+$/` |
| `"only_digits"` | `/^\d+$/` |
| `"match_regex:/pattern/"` | Custom regex |
| literal value | Exact equality |

Use `"skip"` for IDs, timestamps, and any server-generated fields.

## Spec file pattern (`cypress/e2e/api/<domain>.spec.ts`)

```typescript
import { MyDomain } from '../../support/lib/my_domain';
import { verifyResponseCode, verifyResponseIsSuccessful, verifyResponseTemplate } from '../../support/utils/assertions';

describe('MyDomain API', () => {
  const api = new MyDomain();

  it('POST create returns expected shape', async () => {
    const response = await api.create(api.createRequest);
    verifyResponseTemplate(response, api.createResponse, 200);
  });

  it('negative: non-existent returns 404', async () => {
    const response = await api.getById('nonexistent', false);
    verifyResponseCode(response, 404);
  });
});
```

## Assertion guide

- Status code only → `verifyResponseCode(response, 200)`
- Exact body match → `verifyResponse(response, expectedBody, 200)`
- Body with dynamic fields → `verifyResponseTemplate(response, template, 200)`
- Negative test → pass `false` to wrapper method, then assert error code

## Run commands

```bash
npx cypress run                                  # all tests
npx cypress run --spec "cypress/e2e/api/<domain>.spec.ts"        # one file
npx cypress open                                  # open test runner
ENV=qa npx cypress run                           # qa environment
```